  "system": {
    "description": "<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Specializations: </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Specific form of persuasion &mdash; </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">debate, storytelling, flirt, oration</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">.</span></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Persuasion </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">is similar to </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">con </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">and </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">bargain </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">&mdash; and is a little bit of both. A character using </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">persuasion </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">is trying to convince someone to go along with them &mdash; but they aren&rsquo;t tricking the person (that would be </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">con</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">), and they aren&rsquo;t paying them (as in a </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">bargain</span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">).</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\">However, potential rewards can be offered &mdash; talking someone into rescuing a princess from an Imperial holding cell is definitely a </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">persuasion </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">attempt. And stating that the reward would be &ldquo;bigger than anything you can imagine&rdquo; without going into details is not unusual.</span> <br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /><br /></p>",
